GUSAU – No fewer than 2,158 pilgrims from Zamfara State are expected to be in Saudi Arabia for this year’s hajj operation exercise through Abubakar III International Airport in Sokoto. Addressing the first batch of 560 pilgrims from Bungudu, Bukuyyum, Kaura Namoda, Tsafe and Zurmi local government areas at the Hajj camp in Gusau, the state capital on Friday, the state Governor, Alhaji Abdulaziz Yari who spoke through his deputy, Mallam Ibrahim Wakkala urged the intending pilgrims to use the hajj exercise to cry out unto God for divine intervention considering the persistent killings in the state. Governor Yari noted that no society could achieve progress at any level without peace and harmony. He urged them to pray for peace in the state and the country as a whole. According to the governor, the state government has made adequate arrangements regarding their accommodations and health facilities to ensure a successful hajj operation this year. He said that he and other government officials would also be praying for a successful hajj operation. The deputy governor advised the intending pilgrims to ensure that they conduct their affairs according to the tenets of Islamic religion. Earlier, Alhaji Abubakar Sarkin Pawa Dambo, the Chairman of the State Hajj Commission, noted that 2,158 seats were allocated to Zamfara State for this year’s hajj operation from the National Hajj Commission. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 